        <p>A custody or support case can feel impossible if money's tight. The good news: there's a whole ladder of help between "go it completely alone" and "hire an expensive firm." Most dads don't realize how many rungs there are.</p>

        <h2>Free and low-cost options</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Legal aid societies</strong> — nonprofit lawyers who help people under certain income limits, often with family law. Search "[your state] legal aid."</li>
          <li><strong>Court self-help centers</strong> — many family courts have a desk or website with free forms and step-by-step guides.</li>
          <li><strong>Law school clinics</strong> — supervised students handle real cases for free or cheap.</li>
          <li><strong>Bar association referral lines</strong> — often offer a low-cost first consultation.</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="callout">
          <p><strong>Can't afford court fees?</strong> Ask the clerk about a <strong>fee waiver</strong> (sometimes called "in forma pauperis"). If your income qualifies, the court waives filing costs — this is routine, not a favor.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Representing yourself ("pro se")</h2>
        <p>You're allowed to handle your own case, and many dads do. If you go this route:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the court's official forms and instructions — don't reinvent them.</li>
          <li>Stay organized: keep a calm, dated record of everything.</li>
          <li>Consider <strong>"limited scope" / "unbundled" help</strong> — hiring a lawyer for just one piece (reviewing documents, coaching you for a hearing) instead of the whole case. Far cheaper than full representation.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Choosing a family-law attorney</h2>
        <p>If you do hire someone, a short consultation tells you a lot. Good questions to ask:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>How much of your practice is family law / fathers' cases?</li>
          <li>What's your honest read on my situation?</li>
          <li>How do you bill, and what's a realistic total cost?</li>
          <li>Who actually handles my case day to day?</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="callout">
          <p>Need help with a specific issue first? See <a href="{{ '/legal/custody/' | url }}">Custody &amp; Visitation</a> or <a href="{{ '/legal/child-support/' | url }}">Child Support</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <p><em>This page is a starting draft and is general information, not legal advice. Availability of these resources varies by state and county — confirm details locally.</em></p>
